  "text": "The consumer offset commit flow in Apache Kafka traces from KafkaConsumer.commitSync() through multiple components to finally append records to the __consumer_offsets topic.\n\n## Client-Side Flow\n\n1. **KafkaConsumer.commitSync()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer.java:1039) - The public API method delegates to the underlying consumer implementation.\n\n2. **AsyncKafkaConsumer/ClassicKafkaConsumer.commitSync()** - The actual consumer implementation calls commitSync() with optional offsets.\n\n3. **ConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java:1140) - Handles synchronous offset commits with retry logic. This method calls sendOffsetCommitRequest() to send the request to the broker.\n\n4. **ConsumerCoordinator.sendOffsetCommitRequest()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java:1270) - Creates an OffsetCommitRequest with the offsets to be committed and sends it to the group coordinator broker.\n\n## Broker-Side Flow\n\n5. **KafkaApis.handleOffsetCommitRequest()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala:272) - The broker API handler receives the OffsetCommitRequest, performs authorization and validation, then delegates to the GroupCoordinator.commitOffsets() method.\n\n6. **GroupCoordinator.commitOffsets()** (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinator.java:356) - An interface method that defines the offset commit contract.\n\n7. **GroupCoordinatorService.commitOffsets()** (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java:1971) - The implementation that schedules a write operation using CoordinatorRuntime.scheduleWriteOperation() with the coordinator shard address.\n\n8. **GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset()** (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java:852) - Delegates to OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset().\n\n9. **OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset()** (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java:600) - Validates the offset commit request, processes each topic-partition, and creates CoordinatorRecord objects via GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord().\n\n10. **GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord()** (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.java:467) - Creates serialized offset commit records that will be written to the __consumer_offsets topic.\n\n11. **CoordinatorRuntime.scheduleWriteOperation()** (coordinator-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/common/runtime/CoordinatorRuntime.java:2182) - Enqueues the write event for asynchronous processing via the coordinator event processor.\n\n12. **CoordinatorPartitionWriter.append()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/coordinator/group/CoordinatorPartitionWriter.scala:137) - The final step that calls replicaManager.appendRecordsToLeader() to write the offset commit records to the __consumer_offsets topic partition on the leader replica.\n\nThe complete chain ensures that offset commits flow from the consumer client, through the broker's API layer, through the group coordination layer, and finally into the __consumer_offsets topic as durable records that can be replayed during broker startup or when new consumers join the group."
}

